section.section:
Upon renewal of an existing automobile insurance policy, if the insured or a person holding an insurable interest in the subject of the policy requests proof of insurance, an authorized insurer shall provide:
a copy of the automobile insurance policy declarations; or
written proof of the automobile insurance that consists of:
the name and address of the insured and insurer;
a description of the vehicle, including the vehicle identification number, that is the subject of the insurance policy;
a description and the amount, if applicable, of the insurance coverage including applicable deductibles;
the inception and expiration dates of coverage;
the name and address of the person with an insurable interest; and
the premium for the applicable coverage.
